The government is planning to borrow CZK 159.2 billion this year.
At the beginning of December, however, the ministry reduced the plan to 152.8 billion crowns due to better development of the state budget.
The national debt of the Czech Republic rose to 842.7 billion crowns at the end of September.
In the first nine months of this year, it increased by CZK 40.2 billion.
Since June, however, it has decreased by 13.4 billion crowns.
The Ministry of Finance today confirmed its data on the state debt from the beginning of October.
For every Czech, there is a debt of over 84,000 crowns.
