Until recently, several states, including Germany, were against making these nominal documents available to the public, due to the sensitive nature of some information.
What are the alleged homosexuality or mental disability of some of the victims of deportation?
The registers of concentration camps or arrest warrants drawn up by the Gestapo were collected after the war for the practical purpose of finding deported or forced labour subjected to civilians, bringing them evidence of their internment in order to open the way for their compensation.
