Which insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance, which protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense, which depends on various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of the driver's license, the type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurance company will receive the agreed insurance amount in a certain amount for taking over the payment of damages in the event of an insured event.
Insurance is the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driving license, type of vehicle that is insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of checks, insurance companies have concluded that married people have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of the journeys and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The increase in the frequency of rides increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the premium price.
Therefore, the driver must carefully study the situation in order to choose the insurance that best fits his insurance profile.
We will show here the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to meeting the type of insured, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five face various disadvantages, such as little driving experience and a short driving licence, when they want to arrange insurance premiums at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most careful drivers can choose insurance against all risks with a discount of insurance premiums so as to obtain insurance coverage of all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would involve the client’s participation in the insurance event.
"The part of the payment of the insured event provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the price of the insurance premium, which will be the higher, the lower the participation would be," explains Luis Noguera, Chief Executive Officer of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants in the operation so that the client insures against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce your insurance premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
On the other hand, malus is an increase in the mentioned basic rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus,” explains Noguera.
After exceeding the limit of twenty-five years, drivers have it easier when they go to arrange insurance, as the client’s risk index decreases, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people are usually not able to benefit from the experience gained in advance when an accident occurs, or even while driving," says the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when the "newbie's fear" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married, but does not have children yet, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if, of course, his economic situation allows it.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies as the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with an insurance discount (which could be 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other participants in the operation, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
“Their management is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount,” Luis Noguera said.
Pensioners are recommended to have insurance against all risks with a discount of insurance premium (which is 150 euros) or insurance extended to other participants in the operation, if a high bonus has been achieved.
It should be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would suit us most given our personal situation.
